				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I believe that is the reason why Mages chose not to have Dire Charm. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Actually I think the reason we chose not to have it was that there was a VERY limited number of usable targets it would work on, apart from being outside our traditional class areas.
<br />

<br />
When our pets which are level 60 (and higher if focussed) can be matched and sometimes exceeded in performance (defensive and offensive) by a level 45 or 46 charmed mob, something should be looked at and changed.
<br />

<br />
A typical DC mob has 12-16k hp, at a guesstimate, maybe a bit lower.  Our pets are a third to a half of that value, being generous.  There's one thing to be looked at.  DPS output is roughly equivalent, strictly talking DC mobs, however I think our pets should be a step above that.
<br />

<br />
All this has been said before though... I'll leave it at that for now before I work myself up.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_doh.gif" alt="d'oh!" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fazzadien Elementweaver</a> 
